  The Central Organisation of Trade Unions (Cotu) has called on governors in tea-growing counties to revoke 99-year land leases for multinational tea companies. Cotu Secretary General Francis Atwoli accused the firms of sacking workers after introducing tea harvesting machines. ALSO READ:

Cotu boss roots for 2022 fund "The companies are determined to replace human labour with machines," he said. Atwoli said the tea firms should be returned to counties. “Take over or task the Kenya Tea Development Agency to do the job,” he said.